OL,3,CDoomed satellite ERS-2 to crash back
OL,4,Cto Earth - but where will it land?
OL,6,FBut some fragments could reach Earth's
OL,7,Fsurface.
OL,9,FThe UK Space Agency captured images of
OL,10,FERS-2 during its descent. The
OL,11,Fsatellite is falling by more than 10
OL,12,Fkm a day and the speed of its descent
OL,13,Fis increasing rapidly. It is expected
OL,14,Fto reenter the Earth's atmosphere on
OL,15,FWednesday.
OL,17,FWhat is the ERS-2?
OL,19,FThe ERS-2 was launched back in 1995
OL,20,Fand was the most sophisticated
OL,21,Fsatellite ever developed by Europe.
