OL,3,CDoomed satellite ERS-2 to crash back
OL,4,Cto Earth - but where will it land?
OL,6,FIt collected a trove of information on
OL,7,Fland surfaces, oceans and polar caps
OL,8,Fand analysed natural disasters.
OL,10,FWhen did its mission end?
OL,12,FAfter 16 years of successful
OL,13,Foperations the European Space Agency
OL,14,Ftook the decision to end its mission
OL,15,Fand deorbit the satellite.
OL,17,FA number of space manoeuvres were then
OL,18,Fmade to reduce its risk of colliding
OL,19,Fwith other satellites before it
OL,20,Feventually reentered the Earth's
OL,21,Fatmosphere.
