OL,3,CDoomed satellite ERS-2 to crash back
OL,4,Cto Earth - but where will it land?
OL,6,FThe ESA estimates the satellite will
OL,7,Freenter Earth's atmosphere at 11:14
OL,8,FGMT on Wednesday, February 21.
OL,10,FWhere will the satellite crash?
OL,12,FThe satellite is under frequent
OL,13,Fobservation by the ESA but because the
OL,14,Freentry is 'natural', it is impossible
OL,15,Fto predict exactly when and where the
OL,16,Fsatellite will begin to burn up.
OL,18,FThe window during which reentry is
OL,19,Fpossible will continue to shrink until
OL,20,Fthe time of reentry, they said.
