OL,3,CDoomed satellite ERS-2 to crash back
OL,4,Cto Earth - but where will it land?
OL,6,FDespite the fact that experts can't
OL,7,Fpredict where parts of the satellite
OL,8,Fwill hit the Earth, the annual risk of
OL,9,Fan individual human being injured by
OL,10,Fspace debris is under 1 in 100 billion.
OL,12,FNone of the fragments that could hit
OL,13,Fthe Earth contain any toxic or
OL,14,Fradioactive substances, the ESA said.
